Bolton, Berjaya, Premium Nutrients: Malaysia Equity Preview

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-07-11T00:05:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-11/bolton-berjaya-premium-nutrients-malaysia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Malaysia trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The  FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI (FBMKLCI)  Index rose 0.3 percent to
1,594.74 on July 8.        Bolton Bhd. (BOL)  : OSK Trustees Bhd. bought 9.47 million
shares in Bolton, raising its stake in the property developer to
25 million shares, or a 8.8 percent stake, a stock filing
showed. Bolton fell 0.9 percent to 1.12 ringgit.       Berjaya Corp. (BC MK): The property, insurance and gaming
group scrapped plans for a dividend after saying it will
privatize unit Cosway Corp. Ltd. The shares rose 0.8 percent to
1.25 ringgit.        NPC Resources Bhd. (NPC)  : The oil palm plantations
operator and three other parties agreed to sell their holdings
in PT Prasetia Alam Sdn. for $6.37 million, according to a
company statement. NPC rose 4.8 percent to 2.20 ringgit on July
6.        NWP Holdings Bhd. (NWP)  : The Malaysian timber products
maker agreed to form a joint venture to operate a timber
processing business in  Laos , it said in a statement. NWP last
traded at 11 sen on July 6.        Premium Nutrients Bhd. (PRNB)  : The company, which sold
its palm oil processing units, will seek a new business to
maintain its listing. The company has 12 months to submit a
proposal to the Securities Commission or face de-listing, it
said in a statement. The stock gained 18 percent to 23.5 sen.  To contact the reporter on this story:
